> Publish tip: run `npm publish --access public` after building. For scoped packages (`@yourorg/...`) set up your npm org and permissions.

---

# Production migration Job (Kubernetes + Helm hook)

File: `k8s/migrate-job.yaml` (standalone)
```yaml
apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: Job
metadata:
  name: gateway-db-migrate
  namespace: gateway-prod
spec:
  backoffLimit: 3
  template:
    spec:
      serviceAccountName: gateway-sa
      restartPolicy: OnFailure
      containers:
        - name: migrate
          image: ghcr.io/yourorg/blockchain-api-gateway:{{ .Chart.AppVersion | default "latest" }}
          imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
          command: ["node", "/app/dist/scripts/migrate_runner.js"]
          env:
            - name: DATABASE_URL
              valueFrom:
                secretKeyRef:
                  name: gateway-secrets
                  key: DATABASE_URL
            - name: MIGRATION_DIR
              value: "/app/src/db/migrations"
      securityContext:
        runAsNonRoot: true
        runAsUser: 1000
